fields.description:
Hi,

We are developing a brand new addon for *Atlassian Cloud*. We are using the search request view module (https://developer.atlassian.com/static/connect/docs/latest/modules/jira/search-request-view.html) to do some exports on issue navigator, and we have a real problem.
That component requires to configure a url where JIRA will call our addon when a user select our export option on issue navigator.

That call from JIRA to our addon sends a request object, with jwt info of authetication and user info of the user who click our export option. After that, we have the control on our addon code and we are doing some REST calling to JIRA API.

The problem is that, on this Rest calls from our addon to JIRA API, it seems that the user info is working well, because, although the user has configured Spanish language, the JIRA API call is returning me the information in perfect English language. We have done many Rest JIRA callings before and if the user has selected a different language on his profile from English, the info is returned in that language.

I'm following that guide to do the Rest call to JIRA API (https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/atlassian-connect-express#markdown-header-how-to-send-a-signed-outbound-http-request-back-to-the-host). For that, I have tested with this two options of making the Rest call:


{code:java}
First option:
        addon.httpClient.get({
                url: '/rest/api/2/search
            },
            function (err, httpResponse, body) {
                    //myCode
            }
        );
{code}


Second option:

{code:java}
        var httpClient = addon.httpClient({
            clientKey: myClientKey,
            userKey:  myUserKey,
            appKey: myAppKey
        });
        httpClient.get({
                url: '/rest/api/2/search
            },
            function (err, httpResponse, body) {
                    //myCode
            }
        );

{code}

I need that the issue info returned by this Rest JIRA API call is localiced in the user language. When I say the user language, I mean the user that clicks on the export option, the one that is registered on the request object that is send from JIRA to out addon.

Regards.

[This Cloud documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jiracloud/navigating-to-user-directories-735942056.html] says:
{quote}
A user directory is a place where you store information about users and groups. You can also connect to external user directories.
{quote}

However, external user directories are not available in Cloud.
